                <h1>Clara Barton: Pioneer of Nursing and Humanitarian Efforts</h1>
                <p>Clara Barton, known as the "Angel of the Battlefield," was a pioneering nurse and humanitarian. She founded the American Red Cross in 1881 and played a critical role in providing care during the Civil War. Barton's dedication to helping others established a legacy of compassion and service, impacting countless lives and shaping modern nursing.</p>
